SIMPLE: hurter
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hurter
<hw>Hurt"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A bodily injury causing
pain; a wound, bruise, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The pains of sickness and <qex>hurts</qex> . . . all men feel.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An injury causing pain of mind or conscience; a
slight; a stain; as of sin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But the jingling of the guinea helps the <qex>hurt</qex> that
Honor feels.</q> <rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Injury; damage; detriment; harm; mischief.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou dost me yet but little <qex>hurt</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Wound; bruise; injury; harm; damage; loss;
detriment; mischief; bane; disadvantage.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hurter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hurter
<hw>Hurt"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who hurts or does
harm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I shall not be a <qex>hurter</qex>, if no helper.</q>
<rj><qau>Beau. & Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hurter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Hurter
<hw>Hurt"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>heurtoir</ets>, lit., a
striker. See <er>Hurt</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>A butting
piece; a strengthening piece, esp.: <fld>(Mil.)</fld> A piece of wood at
the lower end of a platform, designed to prevent the wheels of gun
carriages from injuring the parapet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hurtful</ent>⟦br⟧
